(472, 'foreground', 'The part of an image or display that is nearest to the viewer.', '', 'n', '', 1, 'core'),
(473, 'foreground application', 'The active program visible in a graphics user interface.', '', 'n', '', 1, 'core'),
(474, 'foreground task', 'The active program on a computer.', 'While a computer may have many programs open at the same time, only one is active.  For example, right now you might have a word processor, an email reader, and a web browser open at the same time.  Because you are using the web browser at this moment, the web browser is the foreground task.', 'n', '', 1, 'core'),
(475, 'form', 'A blank document or template to be filled in by the user. ', 'A form is a document with spaces (fields) in which to write or select, for a series of documents with similar contents. The documents usually have the printed parts in common, possibly except for a serial number. Advantages of forms include:\r\n\r\n    * one has to write less (while the printing is almost universally done in some automatic way)\r\n    * one is told or reminded what information has to be supplied\r\n    * uniformity, for convenience in processing\r\n\r\nA form on a computer allows for conveniently typing in the variable parts (the input data).', 'n', '', 1, 'core'),
(476, 'format', 'The layout of all or part of a document; the type of a computer file.', 'Example 1: Do you want to apply this format to the entire document?\r\n\r\nExample 2: Please send your resume in PDF format.', 'n', '', 1, 'core'),
(477, 'format', 'Determine the arrangement of data or text for storage and display.', 'Example 1: Insert a disk to format into Drive A.\r\n\r\nExample 2: Please format this document in using a smaller font.', 'tv', '3;4;8;9', 1, 'core'),
(478, 'formula', 'Any mathematical rule expressed symbolically.', 'In computing, a formula typically describes a calculation, such as addition, to be performed on two or more variables. A formula is often implicitly provided in the form of a computer instruction such as\r\n\r\n    Total fruit = number of Apples + number of Oranges.\r\n\r\nIn computer spreadsheet terminology, a formula is usually a text string containing cell references, e.g.\r\n\r\n    =A1+A2\r\n\r\nwhere both A1 and A2 describe "cells" (column A, row 1 or 2) within the spreadsheet. The result appears within the cell containing the formula itself (possibly A3, at end of values in column A). The = sign precedes the right hand side of the formula indicating the cell contains a formula rather than data. The left hand side of the formula is, by convention, omitted because the result is always stored in the cell itself and would be redundant.', 'n', '', 1, 'core'),
(479, 'forward', 'Send a received message to someone other than the person who originally sent it.', '', 'tv', '', 1, 'core'),
(480, 'forward', 'Towards the front.', '', 'adj', '', 1, 'core'),
(481, 'frame', 'A section of a web page that loads and functions independently of other sections.', '', 'n', '', 1, 'core'),
(482, 'frameset', 'An invisible Web page that divides a browser window into two or more sections, each with the ability to display a separate page or file.', '', 'n', '', 1, 'core'),
(483, 'freeware', 'Software that is available without cost.', 'Freeware is computer software that is available for use with no cost or for an optional fee. Freeware allows authors to contribute something for the benefit of the community, while at the same time allowing them to retain control of the source code, future direction of development and preserve its business potential. Freeware is different from shareware, where the user is obliged to pay (e.g. after some trial period or for additional functionality).', 'n', '', 1, 'core'),
(484, 'frequency', 'The rate at which something occurs; the level on a spectrum of radio waves at which a signal is broadcast.', '', 'n', '', 1, 'core'),
(485, 'full screen', 'Occupying all the space on a display.', '', 'adj', '', 1, 'core'),
(486, 'full version', 'An edition of a program that contains all features and functionality.', '', 'n', '', 1, 'core'),
(487, 'function', 'A software routine that performs a specific action.', '', 'n', '', 1, 'core'),
