(890, 'redo', 'Execute an action again after it has been reversed.', 'Undo is a command in many computer programs. It erases the last change done to the document reverting it to an older state. In some more advanced programs such as graphic processing, undo will negate the last command done to the file being edited.\r\n\r\nThe opposite of undo is redo. The redo command reverses the undo or advances the buffer to a more current state.', 'tv', '', 1, 'core'),
