(1654, 'decimal place', 'A digit to the right of the decimal point in a decimal. ', 'As an illustration, the decimal quantity 12.345 can be expressed with various numbers of decimal places. If insufficient precision is available then the number is rounded in some manner to fit the available precision. The following table shows the results for 12.345, with rounding, when expressed with differing numbers of decimal places:\r\n\r\n0 decimal place: 12\r\n1 decimal place: 12.3\r\n2 decimal places: 12.35\r\n3 decimal places: 12.345\r\n4 decimal places: 12.3450', 'n', '', 1, 'core'),
