(1705, 'east', 'One of the four principal compass points, specifically 90Â°, conventionally directed to the right on maps; the direction of the rising sun at an equinox. ', 'East is a direction in geography. It is one of the four cardinal directions or compass points, opposite of west and at right angles to north and south. East is the direction toward which the Earth rotates about its axis, and therefore the general direction from which the Sun appears to rise.', 'n', '6', 1, 'core'),
(1706, 'echo', 'A display of the command that has just been executed.', 'In computer terminology, Echo can refer to the following:\r\n\r\n* Echo (command), a Unix, DOS and Microsoft Windows command to display a line of text\r\n* Echo (framework), a web framework for Java programming\r\n* The echo protocol, an internet protocol largely superseded by ping\r\n* A command in programming languages to output one or more strings\r\n* A discussion forum on FidoNet\r\n', 'n', '', 1, 'core'),
(1707, 'edge', 'The outside limit of an object or area.', '', 'n', '', 1, 'core'),
(1708, 'editable', 'Having the possibility of being changed.', '', 'adj', '', 1, 'core'),
(1709, 'edited', 'Altered from a previous version.', '', 'adj', '', 1, 'core'),
(1710, 'editing', 'The preparation of a document or media file for submission or distribution.', 'Editing is the process of preparing language, images, sound, video, or film through correction, condensation, organization, and other modifications in various media. A person who edits is called an editor. In a sense, the editing process originates with the idea for the work itself and continues in the relationship between the author and the editor. Editing is, therefore, also a practice that includes creative skills, human relations, and a precise set of methods.', 'n', '', 1, 'core'),
(1711, 'electronic', 'Using computer hardware and software, or using other circuit-based devices.', 'An electronic component is any physical entity in an electronic system whose intention is to affect the electrons or their associated fields in a desired manner consistent with the intended function of the electronic system. Components are generally intended to be in mutual electromechanical contact, usually by being soldered to a printed circuit board (PCB), to create an electronic circuit with a particular function (for example an amplifier, radio receiver, or oscillator). Components may be packaged singly or in more complex groups as integrated circuits. Some common electronic components are capacitors, resistors, diodes, transistors, etc.', 'adj', '', 1, 'core'),
(1712, 'element', 'A distinct part of a larger whole.', '', 'n', '', 1, 'core'),
(1713, 'ellipse', 'The shape of an oval or an egg.', '', 'n', '', 1, 'core'),
(1714, 'elliptical', 'Shaped like an oval or an egg.', '', 'adj', '', 1, 'core'),
(1715, 'embed', 'Insert one file inside a larger document or file.', 'Example: The instructions showed how to embed a chart from the spreadsheet within the word document', 'tv', '', 1, 'core'),
