(1877, 'localization', 'The process of converting a program to run in a particular geographical area, so that all text is displayed in the native language, and native conventions are used for sorting, formatting, etc.', 'Localization (or localisation) is often abbreviated as L10n, derived from the initial L + 10 letters in the middle + the final n.\r\n\r\nLocalization is the process of adapting a program for a specific international market, which includes translating the user interface, resizing dialog boxes, customizing features (if necessary), and testing results to ensure that the program still works.  For example, a product that is originally designed for an English-speaking market will need a lot of localization work in order to be useful for Chinese speakers - in addition to translation, the product will need to support input and display for Chinese characters.', 'adj', '', 1, 'core'),
