(1939, 'multiply', 'Add a number to itself a certain number of times.', 'Multiplication is the mathematical operation of scaling one number by another. It is one of the four basic operations in elementary arithmetic (the others being addition, subtraction and division).\r\n\r\nMultiplication is defined for whole numbers in terms of repeated addition; for example, 4 multiplied by 3 (often said as "4 times 3") can be calculated by adding 3 copies of 4 together: 4 + 4 + 4 = 12.', 'tv', '', 1, 'core'),
