(2200, 'sensor', 'A device intended to detect a particular stimulus.', 'A sensor is a device that measures a physical quantity and converts it into a signal which can be read by an observer or by an instrument. For example, a mercury thermometer converts the measured temperature into expansion and contraction of a liquid which can be read on a calibrated glass tube.\r\n\r\nSensors are used in everyday objects such as touch-sensitive elevator buttons and lamps which dim or brighten by touching the base. Applications include cars, machines, aerospace, medicine, manufacturing and robotics.', 'n', '', 1, 'core'),
