(2253, 'space bar', 'A long rectangular key at the bottom of a keyboard used to create a blank space in text.', 'A key on an alphanumeric keyboard in the form of a horizontal bar in the lowermost row, significantly wider than other keys. Its main purpose is to conveniently enter the space, e.g., between words during typing. It is large enough so that a thumb from either hand can use it easily.', 'n', '', 1, 'core'),
